<Layout title="Privacy Policy | Prescia IQ" description="Privacy Policy for Prescia IQ — Predict IQ Holdings Pty Ltd (ABN 89 696 793 432).">
  <div class="pt-32 pb-24">
    <SectionWrapper>
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto glass-card p-8 md:p-12">
        <div class="mb-12 border-b border-white/10 pb-8">
          <h1 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground font-sans">Predict IQ Holdings Pty Ltd &mdash; Trading as Prescia IQ &mdash; ABN 89 696 793 432</p>
          <p class="text-primary font-semibold font-sans mt-2">Effective Date: 02 April 2026</p>
        </div>
        <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none font-sans prose-headings:font-display prose-headings:font-bold prose-h2:text-2xl prose-h2:mt-10 prose-h2:mb-4 prose-h2:text-foreground prose-h3:text-lg prose-h3:mt-6 prose-h3:mb-3 prose-h3:text-foreground/90 prose-p:text-muted-foreground prose-p:leading-relaxed prose-li:text-muted-foreground prose-a:text-primary">
          <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
          <p>This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Predict IQ Holdings Pty Ltd</strong> (ABN 89 696 793 432) trading as Prescia IQ collects, uses, discloses, stores, and protects personal information. We comply with the <em>Privacy Act 1988</em> (Cth), the 13 Australian Privacy Principles, and the <em>Spam Act 2003</em> (Cth). This Policy applies to presciaiq.com.au and all sub-brand websites (AdsIQ, BuildPredictIQ, OpsIQ, TradesmanIQ) and related Services.</p>
          <h2>2. What is personal information?</h2>
          <p>Personal information means information or an opinion about an identified individual, or an individual who is reasonably identifiable, whether true or not, and whether recorded in a material form or not.</p>
          <h2>3. Information we collect</h2>
          <h3>3.1 Information you provide to us</h3>
          <ul><li>Contact details (name, email, phone, business name, role, address)</li><li>Account credentials (username, password hash, profile details)</li><li>Billing information (billing contact, address, ABN)</li><li>Communications, enquiries, call recordings (where notified)</li><li>Information submitted via free intelligence audit, lead capture, or strategy call booking</li></ul>
          <h3>3.2 Information collected automatically</h3>
          <ul><li>Device and browser information (IP address, browser type, OS)</li><li>Usage data (pages visited, time on page, links clicked)</li><li>Cookie and tracking data</li><li>Log data (server logs, error reports)</li></ul>
          <h3>3.3 Information received from third parties</h3>
          <ul><li>Third-party integrations (CRM, advertising platforms, accounting software)</li><li>Business partners and referral sources</li><li>Publicly available sources (LinkedIn, ASIC, ABR)</li></ul>
          <h3>3.4 Customer-supplied data</h3>
          <p>Where you use our Services to process data about your customers or employees, you remain the controller of that data. We process it only on your behalf.</p>
          <h3>3.5 Sensitive information</h3>
          <p>We do not intentionally collect sensitive information. If you provide it, you consent to its collection for the purpose provided.</p>
          <h2>4. How we collect personal information</h2>
          <p>Directly from you when you use our Services, register an account, submit a form, or contact us; automatically through cookies and analytics; and from third parties as described above.</p>
          <h2>5. Why we collect and use personal information</h2>
          <ul><li>Provide, operate, and improve our Services</li><li>Create and manage your account</li><li>Process payments and send invoices</li><li>Respond to enquiries and provide support</li><li>Send service-related and marketing communications (where permitted)</li><li>Conduct analytics and research</li><li>Comply with legal obligations</li><li>Protect against fraud and misuse</li></ul>
          <h2>6. Disclosure of personal information</h2>
          <p>We may disclose personal information to our employees and contractors, third-party service providers (hosting, payments, analytics), professional advisers, government agencies where required by law, and prospective buyers in a merger or acquisition. We do not sell personal information.</p>
          <h2>7. Overseas disclosure</h2>
          <p>Some service providers are located overseas (US, EU). We take reasonable steps to ensure they handle information consistently with the APPs. By using our Services, you consent to overseas disclosure.</p>
          <h2>8. Data security</h2>
          <p>We implement reasonable technical and organisational measures including TLS encryption, access controls, and regular security reviews. No internet transmission is completely secure. Report suspected breaches to <a href="mailto:privacy@presciaiq.com.au">privacy@presciaiq.com.au</a>.</p>
          <h2>9. Retention of personal information</h2>
          <p>We retain personal information as long as necessary for the purposes collected, to comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce agreements. We then destroy or de-identify it.</p>
          <h2>10. Cookies and similar technologies</h2>
          <p>We use cookies to keep you logged in, remember preferences, analyse usage, and deliver advertising. You can control cookies through browser settings; disabling them may affect functionality.</p>
          <h2>11. Direct marketing and the Spam Act</h2>
          <p>We may send marketing communications where you have consented or as permitted by the <em>Spam Act 2003</em>. Every email includes an unsubscribe link. Contact <a href="mailto:privacy@presciaiq.com.au">privacy@presciaiq.com.au</a> to opt out. We process opt-out requests within 5 business days.</p>
          <h2>12. Your rights: access and correction</h2>
          <p>You may request access to or correction of your personal information by contacting <a href="mailto:privacy@presciaiq.com.au">privacy@presciaiq.com.au</a>. We respond within 30 days and may require identity verification.</p>
          <h2>13. Privacy rights for non-Australian individuals</h2>
          <p>If you are in the EEA, UK, or California, additional rights under GDPR, UK GDPR, or CCPA may apply. Contact <a href="mailto:privacy@presciaiq.com.au">privacy@presciaiq.com.au</a>.</p>
          <h2>14. Children</h2>
          <p>Our Services are not directed to children under 18. We do not knowingly collect information from children. Contact us to request deletion if you believe we have done so.</p>
          <h2>15. Complaints</h2>
          <p>Contact <a href="mailto:privacy@presciaiq.com.au">privacy@presciaiq.com.au</a>. We acknowledge within 5 business days and aim to resolve within 30 days. Unresolved complaints may be lodged with the OAIC at <a href="https://www.oaic.gov.au" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.oaic.gov.au</a>.</p>
          <h2>16. Changes to this Policy</h2>
          <p>We may update this Policy at any time. Material changes will be notified by email or through the Services. Continued use after the effective date constitutes acceptance.</p>
          <h2>17. Contact us</h2>
          <p><strong>Predict IQ Holdings Pty Ltd</strong>  
Trading as Prescia IQ  
100 Harris St, Pyrmont NSW 2009 AU  
Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@presciaiq.com.au">privacy@presciaiq.com.au</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </SectionWrapper>
  </div>
</Layout>
